: 371.5199890136719, 'text': ' Khaled Ahmed al-Ahmed. So what was he responsible for?'}, {'id': 53, 'start': 372.0, 'end': 378.79998779296875, 'text': \" The army says that this Hamas member was the chief of operations in the terror group's western sector\"}, {'id': 54, 'start': 378.79998779296875, 'end': 384.9599914550781, 'text': ' in southern Lebanon. Important to note that Hamas does have quite a significant presence in Lebanon.'}, {'id': 55, 'start': 386.4800109863281, 'end': 394.55999755859375, 'text': \" It's allied with Hezbollah. And during the war, Israel's targeted many Hamas operatives in Lebanon.\"}, {'id': 56, 'start': 394.55999755859375, 'end': 398.9599914550781, 'text': ' Hamas has also carried out rocket attacks from Lebanon on Israel during the war,'}, {'id': 57, 'start': 399.9200134277344, 'end': 405.1199951171875, 'text': ' suspected even that the recent rocket fire that we saw from Lebanon in the past couple months'}, {'id': 58, 'start': 405.1199951171875, 'end': 410.1600036621094, 'text': ' were actually carried out by Hamas or other Palestinian groups and not Hezbollah themselves.'}, {'id': 59, 'start': 411.8399963378906, 'end': 417.20001220703125, 'text': \" But he's not the first chief of operations, I think, that Israel's killed in Lebanon,\"}, {'id': 60, 'start': 417.20001220703125, 'end': 422.6400146484375, 'text': ' for Hamas that is. There was also another strike a day earlier that killed a Hezbollah commander,'}, {'id': 61, 'start': 423.20001220703125, 'end': 431.3599853515625, 'text': \" Adnan Harb, who the army said was head of logistics in one of the terror group's regional\"}, {'id': 62, 'start': 431.3599853515625, 'end': 437.3599853515625, 'text': \" divisions. And the army says that he was working to sort of restore Hezbollah's capabilities,\"}, {'id': 63, 'start': 437.3599853515625, 'end': 443.6000061035156, 'text': ' restore its infrastructure in the area of southern Lebanon, which is, of course,'}, {'id': 64, 'start': 443.6000061035156, 'end': 449.2799987792969, 'text': ' a violation of the ceasefire agreement. But we are seeing in general in Lebanon,'}, {'id': 65, 'start': 449.8399963378906, 'end': 453.44000244140625, 'text': ' the Lebanese army step up, dismantling more and more Hezbollah infrastructure.'}, {'id': 66, 'start': 454.7200012207031, 'end': 459.44000244140625, 'text': \" There's been daily strikes still against Hezbollah members, but it's definitely,\"}, {'id': 67, 'start': 459.44000244140625, 'end': 463.20001220703125, 'text': \" I think, we're getting to a point where the Lebanese army is taking much more control\"}, {'id': 68, 'start': 463.20001220703125, 'end': 468.6400146484375, 'text': \" over certain areas in the south of the country. I think it can't be overemphasized what you just\"}, {'id': 69, 'start': 468.6400146484375, 'end': 473.3599853515625, 'text': ' said as a throwaway line, that there are still daily strikes in southern Lebanon. And so obviously,'}, {'id': 70, 'start': 473.3599853515625, 'end': 478.8800048828125, 'text': ' Israel is still, even though there is a ceasefire, is still very active on the northern border,'}, {'id': 71, 'start': 478.8800048828125, 'end': 484.79998779296875, 'text': \" both in Lebanon and in Syria, as we've discussed earlier. Now, let's turn to the West Bank. And\"}, {'id': 72, 'start': 484.79998779296875, 'end': 489.20001220703125, 'text': \" during parts of this war, most of the IDF soldiers, according to what you've told me\"}, {'id': 73, 'start': 489.20001220703125, 'end': 494.6400146484375, 'text': ' in previous podcasts, have been stationed in the West Bank. And I wonder if that is still the case.'}, {'id': 74, 'start': 494.6400146484375, 'end': 500.239990234375, 'text': ' But first, tell us about two incidents yesterday in which three soldiers were attacked in the West'}, {'id': 75, 'start': 500.239990234375, 'end': 506.8800048828125, 'text': ' Bank. These two attacks really took place within moments of each other, completely different areas.'}, {'id': 76, 'start': 507.5199890136719, 'end': 516.3200073242188, 'text': \" So in the northern West Bank, near the Rayhan checkpoint, it's sort of on the western side of\"}, {'id': 77, 'start': 516.3200073242188, 'end': 524.6400146484375, 'text': ' the sort of the north of the West Bank, sort of across from Jenin, that area. Two soldiers who'}, {'id': 78, 'start': 524.6400146484375, 'end': 529.1199951171875, 'text': ' were in the area, not at the checkpoint itself, but kind of near the checkpoint, in a vehicle,'}, {'id': 79, 'start': 529.1199951171875, 'end': 535.4400024414062, 'text': ' they came under fire by a Palestinian gunman, wounding two of them seriously. These two soldiers'}, {'id': 80, 'start': 536.4000244140625, 'end': 542.5599975585938, 'text': \" and the attacker have fled the area. We've heard from the army this morning, as we're recording,\"}, {'id': 81, 'start': 542.5599975585938, 'end': 548.0, 'text': ' that a suspect was detained in one of the nearby villages, still investigating if he'}, {'id': 82, 'start': 548.719970703125, 'end': 552.719970703125, 'text': \" actually was the shooter, but he is suspected to be the shooter. So we'll update, of course,\"}, {'id': 83, 'start': 552.719970703125, 'end': 559.8400268554688, 'text': \" when that's confirmed. And then very shortly after this shooting attack in the southern West Bank,\"}, {'id': 84, 'start': 559.8400268554688, 'end': 566.0800170898438, 'text': ' near Hebron, a Palestinian rounds his car into a junction where IDF troops are stationed.'}, {'id': 85, 'start': 567.2000122070312, 'end': 573.8400268554688, 'text': ' He got out of his car and then stabbed one of the soldiers before he was shot. So one officer'}, {'id': 86, 'start': 573.8400268554688, 'end': 579.8400268554688, 'text': ' was moderately hurt in that attack. And again, the stabber was, in this case, he was shot,'}, {'id': 87, 'start': 579.8400268554688, 'end': 585.760009765625, 'text': \" he wasn't able to flee. From what we know, he was critically wounded and also taken to a hospital.\"}, {'id': 88, 'start': 585.760009765625, 'end': 590.8800048828125, 'text': \" So he's in Israeli custody currently. And from what I understand, Manny,\"}, {'id': 89, 'start': 590.8800048828125, 'end': 595.280029296875, 'text': ' these soldiers, or at least part of them, were from reserve units, is that correct?'}, {'id': 90, 'start': 595.280029296875, 'end': 599.8400268554688, 'text': ' Yeah. So the two reservists who were wounded in the northern West Bank were reservists,'}, {'id': 91, 'start': 601.4400024414062, 'end': 605.5999755859375, 'text': ' one from the Home Front Command, one from the Technology and Logistics Directorate.'}, {'id': 92, 'start': 606.9600219726562, 'end': 613.760009765625, 'text': \" And in the south, it wasn't a reservist, it was an IDF officer from the Jordan Valley\"}, {'id': 93, 'start': 613.760009765625, 'end': 618.47998046875, 'text': ' Brigade, but he was operating in the Hebron area. All sorts of manpower reasons they move'}, {'id': 94, 'start': 618.47998046875, 'end': 624.4000244140625, 'text': ' soldiers around in the West Bank. So that leads to my previous question,'}, {'id': 95, 'start': 624.4000244140625, 'end': 629.9199829101562, 'text': ' which we have yet to answer. Are there currently more soldiers in the West Bank than on the other'}, {'id': 96, 'start': 629.9199829101562, 'end': 634.1599731445312, 'text': ' many, many fronts that Israel is currently dealing with? Or has the balance of'}, {'id': 97, 'start': 635.5999755859375, 'end': 642.0, 'text': \" concentration moved again back to the Gaza Strip? So right now, I think there's still\"}, {'id': 98, 'start': 642.0, 'end': 647.4400024414062, 'text': ' more soldiers in the West Bank. In general, if I remember correctly, the normal number of'}, {'id': 99, 'start': 647.4400024414062, 'end': 654.0800170898438, 'text': \" battalions in the West Bank is 13. But it's sort of fluctuated even up to like 25\"}, {'id': 100, 'start': 655.1199951171875, 'end': 658.9600219726562, 'text': \" at certain points. Right now, I don't know the exact number, but it's probably somewhere hovering\"}, {'id': 101, 'start': 658.9600219726562, 'end': 662.9600219726562, 'text': \" between 15 and 20. That's normally the case, at least in the past year during the war.\"}, {'id': 102, 'start': 663.9199829101562, 'end': 668.9600219726562, 'text': \" And in Gaza, currently, there's only eight brigade level teams. And it's hard to say how many\"}, {'id': 103, 'start': 668.9600219726562, 'end': 675.4400024414062, 'text': \" battalions exactly. So I think it's more or less equal now between Gaza and the West Bank,\"}, {'id': 104, 'start': 675.4400024414062, 'end': 679.4400024414062, 'text': \" especially since Israel resumed fighting in Gaza. There's three divisions in Gaza now,\"}, {'id': 105, 'start': 679.4400024414062, 'end': 683.5999755859375, 'text': \" but they're not full divisions. So it's a little bit complicated to sort of calculate this. But\"}, {'id': 106, 'start': 683.5999755859375, 'end': 688.8800048828125, 'text': \" I will say that once this major offensive begins in the next few weeks, if there's no hostage deal,\"}, {'id': 107, 'start': 689.6799926757812, 'end': 695.280029296875, 'text': ' for sure, Gaza will have way more forces than the West Bank and any other front'}, {'id': 108, 'start': 696.239990234375, 'end': 697.5999755859375, 'text': ' that Israel is currently fighting on.'}, {'id': 109, 'start': 698.239990234375, 'end': 701.760009765625, 'text': \" Okay, we're going to go to a short break and then discuss manpower needs.\"}, {'id': 110, 'start': 725.280029296875, 'end': 744.4000244140625, 'text': \" And we're back. I'm Amanda Burchell Dunn here with our military reporter, Emmanuel Fabian.\"}, {'id': 111, 'start': 744.4000244140625, 'end': 749.5999755859375, 'text': \" So due to developments in the Gaza war that we've been discussing in the first half yesterday or\"}, {'id': 112, 'start': 749.5999755859375, 'end': 755.52001953125, 'text': ' this week, Eyal Zamir, the new IDF Chief of Staff, ordered the personnel director to again,'}, {'id': 113, 'start': 755.52001953125, 'end': 762.0800170898438, 'text': ' send out letters to really press the Haredi community to join up to the army to conscript.'}, {'id': 114, 'start': 762.6400146484375, 'end': 765.760009765625, 'text': \" I don't want to be pessimistic. But we've seen in the past that something like what,\"}, {'id': 115, 'start': 765.760009765625, 'end': 768.6400146484375, 'text': ' 3% made it to the induction center. Is that right, Manny?'}, {'id': 116, 'start': 769.4400024414062, 'end': 775.2000122070312, 'text': \" Yeah, the numbers are very low. And the army is... Well, here's the problem. The army can't do very\"}, {'id': 117, 'start': 775.2000122070312, 'end': 780.7999877929688, 'text': \" much about it. It's almost finished sending out 24,000 draft orders to Haredi men. There's\"}, {'id': 118, 'start': 781.6799926757812, 'end': 787.1199951171875, 'text': ' around 70,000 to 80,000 potential conscripts in the ultra-Orthodox community.'}, {'id': 119, 'start': 789.1199951171875, 'end': 792.0800170898438, 'text': \" And in addition to these 24,000 that they're sending out, they also send out,\"}, {'id': 120, 'start': 792.6400146484375, 'end': 797.6799926757812, 'text': ' in general, to anyone turning 16 and a half. Anyone in the country who turns 16 and a half'}, {'id': 121, 'start': 797.6799926757812, 'end': 802.9600219726562, 'text': ' gets a draft order because they go through the whole process and draft at 18. But even then,'}, {'id': 122, 'start': 802.9600219726562, 'end': 810.3200073242188, 'text': ' even among these thousands of orders sent out, the army now has this yearly goal of 4,800'}, {'id': 123, 'start': 811.5999755859375, 'end': 816.7999877929688, 'text': \" Haredi soldiers. And I think it's reached like 1,800 in total. The army really needs\"}, {'id': 124, 'start': 816.7999877929688, 'end': 824.7999877929688, 'text': \" the State of Israel to impose sanctions on those who don't draft. Otherwise, it doesn't matter if\"}, {'id': 125, 'start': 824.7999877929688, 'end': 829.0399780273438, 'text': \" they send out 80,000 more. I don't think we're going to see any change in the number of those\"}, {'id': 126, 'start': 829.0399780273438, 'end': 835.6799926757812, 'text': ' who are actually going to show up. Okay, so one solution, as I teased in our intro earlier,'}, {'id': 127, 'start': 835.6799926757812, 'end': 840.3200073242188, 'text': ' could be through women power. And you wrote a piece a couple weeks ago, actually, that caught'}, {'id': 128, 'start': 840.3200073242188, 'end': 847.760009765625, 'text': ' my eye. And it had all sorts of data of how many women are enlisting into the fighting units that'}, {'id': 129, 'start': 847.760009765625, 'end': 854.1599731445312, 'text': ' they are able to enlist into because women cannot as yet enlist into all of the fighting units. So'}, {'id': 130, 'start': 854.1599731445312, 'end': 858.7999877929688, 'text': \" I'm just going to throw out some of the data and then we'll discuss it. The Border Defense Corps'\"}, {'id': 131, 'start': 858.7999877929688, 'end': 866.8800048828125, 'text': ' Light Infantry Unit saw 129% draft turnout. And the Combat Intelligence Collection Unit,'}, {'id': 132, 'start': 866.8800048828125, 'end': 875.5999755859375, 'text': ' where the surveillance officers served, saw 132% turnout. The Artillery Corps, this actually'}, {'id': 133, 'start': 875.5999755859375, 'end': 884.1599731445312, 'text': \" surprised me, saw 142% draft turnout. And the Air Force's Air Defense Array saw 115%. The Home\"}, {'id': 134, 'start': 884.1599731445312, 'end': 888.6400146484375, 'text': \" Front Command, that's where my daughter is, the Home Front Command Search and Rescue Unit saw\"}, {'id': 135, 'start': 888.6400146484375, 'end': 897.6799926757812, 'text': ' 132%. And the Border Police saw 107%. So several of these units are units that women, traditionally,'}, {'id': 136, 'start': 897.6799926757812, 'end': 902.3200073242188, 'text': \" if you can call it that, have been serving in. I think it's been, what, 20 years or so that women\"}, {'id': 137, 'start': 902.3200073242188, 'end': 908.7999877929688, 'text': ' are really stepping into these fighting roles. Did anything surprise you, Manny, in this array'}, {'id': 138, 'start': 908.7999877929688, 'end': 914.3200073242188, 'text': ' of data that I just listed out? That did surprise me. The Border Police was, I guess,'}, {'id': 139, 'start': 914.3200073242188, 'end': 917.3599853515625, 'text': \" not really low, but it's definitely... Only over 100.\"}, {'id': 140, 'start': 918.0800170898438, 'end': 923.4400024414062, 'text': ' Very interesting that for many, many years, Border Police was the most sought after unit'}, {'id': 141, 'start': 924.0, 'end': 931.760009765625, 'text': ' for both men and especially among female conscripts. Definitely, they wanted to go to'}, {'id': 142, 'start': 931.760009765625, 'end': 936.5599975585938, 'text': ' the Border Police because Border Police for many, many years were accepting female soldiers to their'}, {'id': 143, 'start': 936.5599975585938, 'end': 942.0, 'text': ' ranks. And as part of their national service, they do it in the police. Many thought it was'}, {'id': 144, 'start': 942.0, 'end': 949.0399780273438, 'text': ' preferable than being in the IDF. The Artillery Corps, the main sort of positions that female'}, {'id': 145, 'start': 949.0399780273438, 'end': 955.760009765625, 'text': ' soldiers are serving in is the Sky Riders Unit. They operate these drones that help forces during'}, {'id': 146, 'start': 957.4400024414062, 'end': 965.3599853515625, 'text': \" operations. But they're all above 100% because, essentially, the Army drafts more soldiers than\"}, {'id': 147, 'start': 965.3599853515625, 'end': 969.3599853515625, 'text': ' it needs. It funnels more conscripts than it needs because it assumes that a certain percentage'}, {'id': 148, 'start': 969.3599853515625, 'end': 977.4400024414062, 'text': ' will refuse the positions and go somewhere else. But the motivation appears to be very, very high,'}, {'id': 149, 'start': 977.4400024414062, 'end': 984.239990234375, 'text': \" so you're getting more than they asked for. There are, of course, soldiers who are still refusing\"}, {'id': 150, 'start': 984.239990234375, 'end': 990.3200073242188, 'text': \" certain positions. It can't be ignored. But the percentages are not significant enough to actually\"}, {'id': 151, 'start': 990.4000244140625, 'end': 997.5999755859375, 'text': \" affect the IDF's long-term planning. It is a bit difficult to sort of understand the percentages,\"}, {'id': 152, 'start': 997.5999755859375, 'end': 1004.239990234375, 'text': ' how many troops it is, because last year we saw that in the surveillance soldier units,'}, {'id': 153, 'start': 1005.52001953125, 'end': 1010.239990234375, 'text': ' it was like 200% more than they asked for, but probably because the Army only planned for a very'}, {'id': 154, 'start': 1010.239990234375, 'end': 1015.2000122070312, 'text': \" small amount in that case, and they got way more. So they've adjusted the numbers that they're\"}, {'id': 155, 'start': 1015.6799926757812, 'end': 1021.1199951171875, 'text': \" bringing in. You noted that they can't serve everywhere, and these are sort of the traditional\"}, {'id': 156, 'start': 1021.1199951171875, 'end': 1026.6400146484375, 'text': \" units. So, interestingly, this draft period, the March-April draft period, the Army's opened up a\"}, {'id': 157, 'start': 1026.6400146484375, 'end': 1033.43994140625, 'text': \" new program as well for female soldiers to serve in, in a combat position, that is, and that's in\"}, {'id': 158, 'start': 1033.43994140625, 'end': 1041.8399658203125, 'text': ' the Intelligence Unit 504, which specializes in human intelligence. This unit used to be very'}, {'id': 159, 'start': 1041.8399658203125, 'end': 1049.9200439453125, 'text': \" small. The Army didn't operate that many human intelligence sources. Even in Gaza, there was a\"}, {'id': 160, 'start': 1049.9200439453125, 'end': 1055.1199951171875, 'text': \" period of about 10 years that Israel didn't have any human sources in Gaza. But during the war,\"}, {'id': 161, 'start': 1055.1199951171875, 'end': 1061.280029296875, 'text': ' because of the use of this unit so much in Gaza, detaining Hamas operatives in Gaza and'}, {'id': 162, 'start': 1061.280029296875, 'end': 1066.239990234375, 'text': \" interrogating them and activating sources in Gaza, they've expanded the unit quite significantly,\"}, {'id': 163, 'start': 1066.800048828125, 'end': 1072.56005859375, 'text': \" which we've previously reported on. The commander of the unit's been promoted another rank up,\"}, {'id': 164, 'start': 1072.56005859375, 'end': 1076.719970703125, 'text': \" so they've basically made the unit much bigger. And now they've also added this new program for\"}, {'id': 165, 'start': 1076.719970703125, 'end': 1083.3599853515625, 'text': \" female soldiers to serve in combat positions in this pretty elite unit. So that's, I think,\"}, {'id': 166, 'start': 1084.0799560546875, 'end': 1088.1600341796875, 'text': \" quite a significant move that the Army's making here. I definitely think it will,\"}, {'id': 167, 'start': 1088.1600341796875, 'end': 1091.9200439453125, 'text': \" it will work, and there'll be a lot of soldiers who want to go and serve there.\"}, {'id': 168, 'start': 1091.9200439453125, 'end': 1100.3199462890625, 'text': \" So you discussed that there was a new unit that was opened up, the 504, but there's also another\"}, {'id': 169, 'start': 1100.3199462890625, 'end': 1107.280029296875, 'text': ' new-ish unit or a revived unit that you just reported on, and its goal is to provide a new'}, {'id': 170, 'start': 1107.280029296875, 'end': 1114.47998046875, 'text': ' operational solution for the threat of UAVs and drones. So about 20 years ago or so, this unit was'}, {'id': 171, 'start': 1115.0400390625, 'end': 1121.0400390625, 'text': ' shut down. And so what was the need to reopen it and reinstate this unit?'}, {'id': 172, 'start': 1121.8399658203125, 'end': 1126.800048828125, 'text': ' So if you remember, during the fighting in Lebanon, one of the most significant threats was'}, {'id': 173, 'start': 1126.800048828125, 'end': 1132.6400146484375, 'text': \" Hezbollah's drones. We saw many, many times that Hezbollah's drones managed to evade Israeli air\"}, {'id': 174, 'start': 1132.6400146484375, 'end': 1137.8399658203125, 'text': ' defence systems, managed to strike sometimes very deep into Israel. There was the attack on the'}, {'id': 175, 'start': 1138.6400146484375, 'end': 1142.800048828125, 'text': \" Golani Brigade, a training base that killed four soldiers. There was a strike on Israel's\"}, {'id': 176, 'start': 1144.1600341796875, 'end': 1148.9599609375, 'text': ' surveillance balloon in the north as well, you know, 80 kilometres into Israel.'}, {'id': 177, 'start': 1150.8800048828125, 'end': 1156.239990234375, 'text': ' And the Army faced, or specifically the Air Force faced quite a challenge when it came to'}, {'id': 178, 'start': 1156.239990234375, 'end': 1161.0400390625, 'text': ' intercepting these drones and tracking these drones and shooting them down. They were doing'}, {'id': 179, 'start': 1161.0400390625, 'end': 1167.5999755859375, 'text': ' it mostly with the Iron Dome, which is kind of expensive to do for small drones, or fighter jets'}, {'id': 180, 'start': 1167.5999755859375, 'end': 1170.800048828125, 'text': ' that they would fly and try to track them down, or helicopters sometimes would track them down'}, {'id': 181, 'start': 1170.800048828125, 'end': 1177.9200439453125, 'text': ' and shoot them down. So a year ago, the Air Force decided that it would start bringing back'}, {'id': 182, 'start': 1179.1199951171875, 'end': 1185.9200439453125, 'text': ' older and different types of air defence systems. For example, gun-based systems like the Vulcan.'}, {'id': 183, 'start': 1185.9200439453125, 'end': 1192.1600341796875, 'text': \" It's basically a machine gun, a big machine gun that can shoot things down and you can station\"}, {'id': 184, 'start': 1192.1600341796875, 'end': 1196.9599609375, 'text': ' at a certain point next to critical infrastructure, next to an army base. And then when anything'}, {'id': 185, 'start': 1196.9599609375, 'end': 1201.43994140625, 'text': \" approaches, you shoot it down basically. And it's a lot more effective for dealing with these\"}, {'id': 186, 'start': 1201.43994140625, 'end': 1205.9200439453125, 'text': ' small targets and a lot more effective at dealing with protecting a specific small area, like a'}, {'id': 187, 'start': 1205.9200439453125, 'end': 1214.0, 'text': ' sensitive facility. Israel also has this in-development laser system, the Iron Beam.'}, {'id': 188, 'start': 1214.0, 'end': 1217.8399658203125, 'text': \" It's supposed to be deployed this year, according to the Defence Ministry, so it's definitely been\"}, {'id': 189, 'start': 1217.8399658203125, 'end': 1222.4000244140625, 'text': \" in testing over the past few years. And again, that's also something that's very effective\"}, {'id': 190, 'start': 1222.4000244140625, 'end': 1232.0, 'text': ' against small targets, like drones, in very short ranges. So the army announced this week that it'}, {'id': 191, 'start': 1232.0, 'end': 1238.9599609375, 'text': ' had reopened the 946th Air Defence Battalion. It was closed in 2003, like you mentioned, more than'}, {'id': 192, 'start': 1238.9599609375, 'end': 1248.56005859375, 'text': \" 20 years ago. It used to operate the Chaparral. It's an American surface-to-air missile system\"}, {'id': 193, 'start': 1248.56005859375, 'end': 1254.3199462890625, 'text': ' for shooting down planes, but it was closed because it was not needed anymore.'}, {'id': 194, 'start': 1254.9599609375, 'end': 1258.8800048828125, 'text': \" But now they've reopened the unit and they're going to be operating, the army hasn't detailed\"}, {'id': 195, 'start': 1258.8800048828125, 'end': 1264.0, 'text': ' which systems, but they say systems that are sort of adapted and tailored for the threat of'}, {'id': 196, 'start': 1264.9599609375, 'end': 1271.52001953125, 'text': \" drones. And they're also going to be very mobile so that the unit can move around with troops.\"}, {'id': 197, 'start': 1271.52001953125, 'end': 1278.239990234375, 'text': \" So if troops are operating beyond the borderline, if they're operating in inside enemy territory,\"}, {'id': 198, 'start': 1278.719970703125, 'end': 1284.1600341796875, 'text': ' this unit can join them with their systems and protect the forces from the drone threat,'}, {'id': 199, 'start': 1284.1600341796875, 'end': 1287.9200439453125, 'text': \" because that's also been a big problem. When troops are operating inside enemy territory,\"}, {'id': 200, 'start': 1288.9599609375, 'end': 1295.43994140625, 'text': \" being able to detect and shoot down drones is much more difficult. So that's the goal of this\"}, {'id': 201, 'start': 1296.4000244140625, 'end': 1304.4000244140625, 'text': \" new unit. There's been a big overhaul in the Air Force's aerial defence. During the war, they've\"}, {'id': 202, 'start': 1304.9599609375, 'end': 1308.6400146484375, 'text': \" reopened units and closed units. They shut down the Patriots because that wasn't being\"}, {'id': 203, 'start': 1308.6400146484375, 'end': 1316.47998046875, 'text': \" used anymore. They've reopened more Iron Dome units. And now this, this new battalion specifically\"}, {'id': 204, 'start': 1316.47998046875, 'end': 1320.800048828125, 'text': ' for shooting down drones, specifically on the northern border, where the drone threat is the'}, {'id': 205, 'start': 1320.800048828125, 'end': 1327.1199951171875, 'text': ' most, I guess, potent. And as you reported, it is as well open to women, correct? Yeah,'}, {'id': 206, 'start': 1327.1199951171875, 'end': 1333.6800537109375, 'text': ' of course. The entire aerial defence array is open for women. So this specific battalion will have'}, {'id': 207, 'start': 1333.6800537109375, 'end': 1338.1600341796875, 'text': ' hundreds of soldiers, and it will be both men and women. In the aerial defence array,'}, {'id': 208, 'start': 1338.1600341796875, 'end': 1344.9599609375, 'text': \" if I remember correctly, it's about 50-50 between men and women serving. Whereas, let's say in the\"}, {'id': 209, 'start': 1344.9599609375, 'end': 1350.0799560546875, 'text': \" Home Front Command Search and Rescue, it's more like 70-30, 70 women, 30% men usually,\"}, {'id': 210, 'start': 1350.0799560546875, 'end': 1356.47998046875, 'text': \" in most of the units. So Manny, as I said at the beginning, if the manpower doesn't arrive,\"}, {'id': 211, 'start': 1356.47998046875, 'end': 1361.5999755859375, 'text': ' perhaps we do need to turn to the woman power. Manny, thank you so much for joining me today.'}, {'id': 212, 'start': 1361.5999755859375, 'end': 1362.719970703125, 'text': ' Thank you.'}]}"